{
  "texts": [
    "-RQ3: What learning outcomes have been demonstrated in studies on AI K-12 learning tools?",
    "-RQ4: What are the research and assessment methods used in studies on AI K-12 learning tools?",
    "This study follows the same four steps employed in other studies on AI literacy in K-12 (e.g., Ng et al., 2022; Su et al., 2022): (1) identifying relevant studies, (2) selecting and excluding eligible studies, (3) data analysis, and (4) reporting findings.",
    "In this study, the preferred reporting items for systematic reviews and meta-analyses (PRISMA) guidelines (Moher et al., 2015) are followed.",
    "The electronic databases used for the literature search were ACM, EBSCO, Web of Science, and Scopus."
  ]
}